## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- [Bun](https://bun.sh) runtime installed
- {{PROVIDER}} API key

### Installation

1. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   bun install
   ```

2. Set up your environment variables:
   ```bash
   cp .env.example .env
   # Edit .env and add your {{ENV_VAR_NAME}}
   ```

### Usage

#### Development Mode

Run the interactive development chat:
```bash
bun run dev
```

#### Server Mode

Start the HTTP server:
```bash
bun run server
```

The server will start on `http://localhost:3000` with the following endpoints:
- `POST /v1/chat/completions` - OpenAI-compatible chat API
- `POST /chat` - Simplified chat endpoint
- `POST /message` - General message processing
- `GET /agents` - List all agents
- `GET /intents` - List all intents
- `GET /tools` - List all tools

#### Using Config Files

You can also use a config file to define your agents, intents, and tools:

```bash
bun run server --config src/config.json
```

